Current steps:
x -> GAP -> reshape -> LN -> sigmoid -> reshape -> multiply with y=x

If I change GAP to both GAP and GMP (Global Max Pooling), concatenate them, then apply LN on the combined features. Then proceed as before.

So, in the forward pass, compute both avg and max pools, concatenate along channels, then process through LN and sigmoid.

This would increase the number of channels processed by LN, potentially capturing more information.

