Then combine x_avg and x_max, say by averaging or concatenating.

Wait, but if I concatenate, again the dimension issue arises. So perhaps sum them element-wise.

So x = (x_avg + x_max) / 2

Then apply sigmoid.

That way, the number of channels remains the same.

Yes, that could work.

